xt\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating API details**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering crafting details for the API in NodeBase and maybe looking into using `toString` values. I also think it’s important to inspect the behavior of NodeImpl to ensure it functions correctly and to assert that the implementation is accurate. This way, I can make sure everything is working as intended before moving forward! There’s a lot to think about here to get it right.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_OUpTVs5XhCrxkFfKw6J3JkBk|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b7481a3935821003339a1ba\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/tmp/xmlpath-src-550/io/restassured/internal/path/xml/NodeImpl.java\", \"limit\": 260}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_QQwYLRSIBhoJXfxKf2ECzV4w|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b8481a3bd01e10a56a2f8dc\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/tmp/xmlpath-src-550/io/restassured/internal/path/xml/NodeChildrenImpl.java\", \"limit\": 260}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_jbCfPBZvJ29A7AspUd2o1VUk|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b8c81a3b367424db9c28b85\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/tmp/xmlpath-src-550/io/restassured/internal/path/xml/NodeBase.java\", \"limit\": 300}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 386, \"output\": 669, \"cacheRead\": 26624, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 27679, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778341162873, \"responseId\": \"resp_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff552b561481a3a99479b4211a67fe\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_OUpTVs5XhCrxkFfKw6J3JkBk|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b7481a3935821003339a1ba\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright 2019 the original author or authors.\\n *\\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \\\"License\\\");\\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\\n *\\n *        http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\\n *\\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \\\"AS IS\\\" BASIS,\\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n * limitations under the License.\\n */\\n\\npackage io.restassured.internal.path.xml;\\n\\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertParameter;\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node;\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.NodeChildren;\\n\\nimport java.util.*;\\n\\nclass NodeImpl extends NodeBase implements Node {\\n\\n    Map<String, String> attributes = new HashMap<>();\\n    NodeChildrenImpl children = new NodeChildrenImpl();\\n    String name;\\n    String value = null;\\n    Object groovyNode;\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Map<String, String> attributes() {\\n        return Collections.unmodifiableMap(attributes);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public String name() {\\n        return name;\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Iterator<String> iterator() {\\n        if (!children.isEmpty()) {\\n            return children.iterator();\\n        } else {\\n            return new ValueIterator();\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public String toString() {\\n        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();\\n        if (children.isEmpty()) {\\n            builder.append(value);\\n        } else {\\n            for (Object next : children) {\\n                builder.append(next);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return builder.toString();\\n    }\\n\\n    /**\\n     * The the Node on the nth index\\n     *\\n     * @param index The index of the node the get\\n     * @return The node\\n     */\\n    public Node get(int index) {\\n        return children.get(index);\\n    }\\n\\n    public NodeChildren children() {\\n        return children;\\n    }\\n\\n    public String getAttribute(String name) {\\n        AssertParameter.notNull(name, \\\"name\\\");\\n        if (!name.startsWith(\\\"@\\\")) {\\n            name = \\\"@\\\" + name;\\n        }\\n        return (String) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    float getFloat(String name) {\\n        return (float) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    double getDouble(String name) {\\n        return (double) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    char getChar(String name) {\\n        return (char) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    boolean getBoolean(String name) {\\n        return (boolean) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    long getLong(String name) {\\n        return (long) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    int getInt(String name) {\\n        return (int) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    short getShort(String name) {\\n        return (short) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    byte getByte(String name) {\\n        return (byte) get(name);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object get(String name) {\\n        if (name.startsWith(\\\"@\\\")) {\\n            return attributes.get(name.substring(1));\\n        }\\n        return get(name, children.nodeIterator(), false);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object getPath(String path) {\\n        XMLAssertion xmlAssertion = new XMLAssertion();\\n        xmlAssertion.setKey(path);\\n        return xmlAssertion.getChildResultAsJavaObject(groovyNode);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public String value() {\\n        return value;\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public <T> List<T> getList(String name) {\\n        return get(name, children.nodeIterator(), true);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object getBackingGroovyObject() {\\n        return groovyNode;\\n    }\\n\\n    @SuppressWarnings(\\\"unused\\\")\\n    Object leftShift(Node node) {\\n        return children.leftShift(node);\\n    }\\n\\n    class ValueIterator implements Iterator<String> {\\n        boolean hasNext = true;\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean hasNext() {\\n            return hasNext;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public String next() {\\n            hasNext = false;\\n            return value;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void remove() {\\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778341175432}, {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_QQwYLRSIBhoJXfxKf2ECzV4w|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b8481a3bd01e10a56a2f8dc\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright 2019 the original author or authors.\\n *\\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \\\"License\\\");\\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\\n *\\n *        http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\\n *\\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \\\"AS IS\\\" BASIS,\\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n * limitations under the License.\\n */\\n\\n\\npackage io.restassured.internal.path.xml;\\n\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node;\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.NodeChildren;\\n\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\\nimport java.util.Iterator;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nclass NodeChildrenImpl extends NodeBase implements NodeChildren {\\n    public List<Node> nodeList = new ArrayList<>();\\n    public Object groovyNodes;\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Node get(int index) {\\n        return nodeList.get(index);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public int size() {\\n        return nodeList.size();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public boolean isEmpty() {\\n        return nodeList.isEmpty();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Iterator<String> iterator() {\\n        return new NodeListIterator(nodeList.iterator());\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public String toString() {\\n        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();\\n        nodeList.forEach(it -> builder.append(it.toString()));\\n        return builder.toString();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Iterable<Node> nodeIterable() {\\n        return nodeList;\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object get(String name) {\\n        return get(name, nodeList.iterator(), false);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object getPath(String path) {\\n        XMLAssertion xmlAssertion = new XMLAssertion();\\n        xmlAssertion.setKey(path);\\n        return xmlAssertion.getChildResultAsJavaObject(groovyNodes);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Iterator<Node> nodeIterator() {\\n        return nodeList.iterator();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public List<Node> list() {\\n        return Collections.unmodifiableList(nodeList);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public <T> List<T> getList(String name) {\\n        return get(name, nodeList.iterator(), true);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public Object getBackingGroovyObject() {\\n        return groovyNodes;\\n    }\\n\\n    @SuppressWarnings(\\\"unused\\\")\\n    Object leftShift(Node node) {\\n        nodeList.add(node);\\n        return nodeList;\\n    }\\n\\n    static class NodeListIterator implements Iterator<String> {\\n        private final Iterator<Node> iterator;\\n\\n        public NodeListIterator(Iterator<Node> nodeList) {\\n            this.iterator = nodeList;\\n        }\\n\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean hasNext() {\\n            return iterator.hasNext();\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public String next() {\\n            return iterator.next().toString();\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void remove() {\\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778341175432}, {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_jbCfPBZvJ29A7AspUd2o1VUk|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff55373b8c81a3b367424db9c28b85\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"package io.restassured.internal.path.xml;\\n\\nimport java.lang.*;\\nimport java.io.*;\\nimport java.net.*;\\nimport java.util.*;\\nimport groovy.lang.*;\\nimport groovy.util.*;\\n\\npublic abstract class NodeBase\\n  extends java.lang.Object  implements\\n    io.restassured.path.xml.element.PathElement,    groovy.lang.GroovyObject {\\npublic  groovy.lang.MetaClass getMetaClass() { return (groovy.lang.MetaClass)null;}\\npublic  void setMetaClass(groovy.lang.MetaClass mc) { }\\npublic  java.lang.Object invokeMethod(java.lang.String method, java.lang.Object arguments) { return null;}\\npublic  java.lang.Object getProperty(java.lang.String property) { return null;}\\npublic  void setProperty(java.lang.String property, java.lang.Object value) { }\\n@java.lang.Override() public abstract  java.lang.Object get(java.lang.String name);\\npublic abstract <T> java.util.List<T> getList(java.lang.String name);\\nprotected static <T> T get(java.lang.String name, java.lang.Object iterator, boolean forceList) { return null;}\\npublic abstract  java.lang.Object getPath(java.lang.String path);\\n@java.lang.Override() public  java.lang.Object getPath(java.lang.String path, java.lang.Class explicitType) { return null;}\\npublic  io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node getNode(java.lang.String name) { return (io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node)null;}\\npublic  java.util.List<io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node> getNodes(java.lang.String name) { return (java.util.List)null;}\\npublic abstract  java.lang.Object getBackingGroovyObject();\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778341175432}]}\n../2680-eaceaea7/human-intervention-logs/io.rest-assured:xml-path:5.5.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-09T15-40-48-674779Z.log:2974:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/io.rest-assured/xml-path/5.5.0/src/test/groovy/io_rest_assured/xml_path/Xml_pathTest.groovy\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage io_rest_assured.xml_path\\n\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.XmlPath\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.config.XmlPathConfig\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.NodeChildren\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.exception.XmlPathException\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir\\nimport org.xml.sax.InputSource\\n\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\n\\nimport static io.restassured.path.xml.XmlPath.CompatibilityMode.HTML\\nimport static io.restassured.path.xml.config.XmlPathConfig.xmlPathConfig\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy\\n\\npublic class Xml_pathTest {\\n    private static final String CATALOG_XML = '''\\\\\\n        <catalog generated=\\\"true\\\">\\n          <book id=\\\"b1\\\" category=\\\"reference\\\">\\n            <title>Effective XML</title>\\n            <price>39</price>\\n            <published>2022-01-05</published>\\n            <available>true</available>\\n            <code>A</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <book id=\\\"b2\\\" category=\\\"fiction\\\">\\n            <title>Native Tales</title>\\n            <price>12</price>\\n            <published>2021-11-10</published>\\n            <available>false</available>\\n            <code>B</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <book id=\\\"b3\\\" category=\\\"reference\\\">\\n            <title>Groovy Paths</title>\\n            <price>27</price>\\n            <published>2023-03-18</published>\\n            <available>true</available>\\n            <code>C</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <metrics>\\n            <smallByte>7</smallByte>\\n            <shortNumber>32000</shortNumber>\\n            <longNumber>922337203685477580</longNumber>\\n            <floatNumber>3.5</floatNumber>\\n            <doubleNumber>19.25</doubleNumber>\\n            <uuid>123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000</uuid>\\n          </metrics>\\n        </catalog>\\n        '''\\n\\n    @AfterEach\\n    void resetGlobalConfiguration() {\\n        XmlPath.reset()\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void readsScalarValuesListsMapsAndParameterizedGPathExpressions() {\\n        XmlPath xmlPath = XmlPath.from(CATALOG_XML)\\n\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getString('catalog.@generated')).isEqualTo('true')\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getInt('catalog.book.size()')).isEqualTo(3)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getBoolean('catalog.book[0].available')).isTrue()\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getChar('catalog.book[2].code')).isEqualTo('C' as char)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getByte('catalog.metrics.smallByte')).isEqualTo((byte) 7)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getShort('catalog.metrics.shortNumber')).isEqualTo((short) 32000)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getLong('catalog.metrics.longNumber')).isEqualTo(922337203685477580L)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getFloat('catalog.metrics.floatNumber')).isEqualTo(3.5F)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getDouble('catalog.metrics.doubleNumber')).isEqualTo(19.25D)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getUUID('catalog.metrics.uuid').toString()).isEqualTo('123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000')\\n\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getList('catalog.book.title', String))\\n                .containsExactly('Effective XML', 'Native Tales', 'Groovy Paths')\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getList('catalog.book.price', Integer))\\n                .containsExactly(39, 12, 27)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getMap('catalog.book[0].attributes()', String, String))\\n                .containsEntry('id', 'b1')\\n                .containsEntry('category', 'reference')\\n\\n        XmlPath withParameter = xmlPath.param('maximumPrice', 30)\\n        assertThat(withParameter.getList('catalog.book.findAll { it.price.toInteger() <= maximumPrice }.collect { it.@id.toString() }', String))\\n                .containsExactly('b2', 'b3')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void exposesRootNodesNodeChildrenAndRelativeGPathNavigation() {\\n        XmlPath xmlPath = new XmlPath(CATALOG_XML)\\n\\n        Node root = xmlPath.get()\\n        assertThat(root.name()).isEqualTo('catalog')\\n        assertThat(root.getAttribute('generated')).isEqualTo('true')\\n        assertThat(root.children().size()).isEqualTo(4)\\n        assertThat(root.children().isEmpty()).isFalse()\\n\\n        Node firstBook = xmlPath.getNode('catalog.book[0]')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.name()).isEqualTo('book')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.attributes())\\n                .containsEntry('id', 'b1')\\n                .containsEntry('category', 'reference')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getNode('title').value()).isEqualTo('Effective XML')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getNodes('title')).hasSize(1)\\n        assertThat(firstBook.get('@category')).isEqualTo('reference')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getPath('price', Integer)).isEqualTo(39)\\n        assertThat(firstBook.iterator().next()).isEqualTo('Effective XML')\\n\\n        NodeChildren books = xmlPath.getNodeChildren('catalog.book')\\n        assertThat(books.size()).isEqualTo(3)\\n        assertThat(books.get(1).getAttribute('id')).isEqualTo('b2')\\n        assertThat(books.list()).extracting { Node node -> node.getAttribute('category') }\\n                .containsExactly('reference', 'fiction', 'reference')\\n        assertThat(books.nodeIterable()).extracting { Node node -> node.getNode('title').value() }\\n                .containsExactly('Effective XML', 'Native Tales', 'Groovy Paths')\\n        assertThat(books.nodeIterator().next().name()).isEqualTo('book')\\n        assertThat(books.getPath('findAll { it.@category == \\\"reference\\\" }.title.collect { it.text() }'))\\n                .isEqualTo(['Effective XML', 'Groovy Paths'])\\n        assertThat(books.iterator().next()).contains('Effective XML')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void supportsRootPathAndInputSources(@TempDir Path tempDir) {\\n        String xml = '<root><items><item id=\\\"1\\\">alpha</item><item id=\\\"2\\\">beta</item></items></root>'\\n        Path xmlFile = tempDir.resolve('document.xml')\\n        Files.writeString(xmlFile, xml, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)\\n\\n        XmlPath rootedPath = XmlPath.with(xml).setRootPath('root.items')\\n        assertThat(rootedPath.getInt('item.size()')).isEqualTo(2)\\n        assertThat(rootedPath.getString('item[1]')).isEqualTo('beta')\\n\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.given(new ByteArrayInputStream(xml.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))).getString('root.items.item[0]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('alpha')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(new StringReader(xml)).getString('root.items.item[1].@id'))\\n                .isEqualTo('2')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.with(new InputSource(new StringReader(xml))).getInt('root.items.item.size()'))\\n                .isEqualTo(2)\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.given(xmlFile.toFile()).getString('root.items.item[0]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('alpha')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(xmlFile.toUri()).getString('root.items.item[1]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('beta')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void appliesNamespacesDoctypeSettingsAndGlobalConfigurationReset() {\\n        String namespacedXml = '''\\\\\\n            <store xmlns:bk=\\\"urn:books\\\">\\n              <bk:book bk:id=\\\"n1\\\"><bk:title>Namespaced Book</bk:title></bk:book>\\n            </store>\\n            '''\\n        XmlPathConfig namespaceConfig = xmlPathConfig().declaredNamespace('bk', 'urn:books')\\n        XmlPath namespacedPath = new XmlPath(namespacedXml).using(namespaceConfig)\\n\\n        assertThat(namespacedPath.getString(\\\"store.'bk:book'.'bk:title'\\\")).isEqualTo('Namespaced Book')\\n        assertThat(namespaceConfig.declaredNamespaces()).containsEntry('bk', 'urn:books')\\n        assertThat(namespaceConfig.isNamespaceAware()).isTrue()\\n\\n        String documentWithInternalDtd = '''\\\\\\n            <!DOCTYPE note [\\n              <!ELEMENT note (message)>\\n              <!ELEMENT message (#PCDATA)>\\n            ]>\\n            <note><message>Hello from DTD</message></note>\\n            '''\\n        assertThatThrownBy { new XmlPath(documentWithInternalDtd).getString('note.message') }\\n                .isInstanceOf(XmlPathException)\\n\\n        XmlPathConfig dtdConfig = xmlPathConfig().allowDocTypeDeclaration(true).disableLoadingOfExternalDtd()\\n        assertThat(new XmlPath(documentWithInternalDtd).using(dtdConfig).getString('note.message'))\\n                .isEqualTo('Hello from DTD')\\n        assertThat(dtdConfig.features())\\n                .containsEntry('http://apache.org/xml/features/nonvalidating/load-external-dtd', false)\\n\\n        XmlPath.config = dtdConfig\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(documentWithInternalDtd).getString('note.message'))\\n                .isEqualTo('Hello from DTD')\\n        XmlPath.reset()\\n        assertThatThrownBy { XmlPath.from(documentWithInternalDtd).getString('note.message') }\\n                .isInstanceOf(XmlPathException)\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void parsesLenientHtmlAndRendersPrettyXml() {\\n        String html = '<html><body><main><h1>REST Assured</h1><a href=\\\"/xml\\\">XML</a><a href=\\\"/json\\\">JSON</a></main></body></html>'\\n        XmlPath htmlPath = new XmlPath(HTML, html)\\n\\n        assertThat(htmlPath.getString('html.body.main.h1')).isEqualTo('REST Assured')\\n        assertThat(htmlPath.getList('html.body.main.a.@href', String)).containsExactly('/xml', '/json')\\n        assertThat(htmlPath.getString('html.body.main.a[1]')).isEqualTo('JSON')\\n\\n        String prettified = XmlPath.with('<root><child attribute=\\\"value\\\">text</child></root>').prettify()\\n        assertThat(prettified)\\n                .contains('<root>')\\n                .contains('<child attribute=\\\"value\\\">text</child>')\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n../2680-eaceaea7/human-intervention-logs/io.rest-assured:xml-path:5.5.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-09T15-40-48-674779Z.log:2975:[tool-call] end id=call_sRX4CsSIJpRYoNVHG2KcY2ka|fc_02855ba501e27c0b0169ff555369a481a3923680d067a02c81 name=write args={\"path\": \"tests/src/io.rest-assured/xml-path/5.5.0/src/test/groovy/io_rest_assured/xml_path/Xml_pathTest.groovy\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage io_rest_assured.xml_path\\n\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.XmlPath\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.config.XmlPathConfig\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.Node\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.element.NodeChildren\\nimport io.restassured.path.xml.exception.XmlPathException\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir\\nimport org.xml.sax.InputSource\\n\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\n\\nimport static io.restassured.path.xml.XmlPath.CompatibilityMode.HTML\\nimport static io.restassured.path.xml.config.XmlPathConfig.xmlPathConfig\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy\\n\\npublic class Xml_pathTest {\\n    private static final String CATALOG_XML = '''\\\\\\n        <catalog generated=\\\"true\\\">\\n          <book id=\\\"b1\\\" category=\\\"reference\\\">\\n            <title>Effective XML</title>\\n            <price>39</price>\\n            <published>2022-01-05</published>\\n            <available>true</available>\\n            <code>A</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <book id=\\\"b2\\\" category=\\\"fiction\\\">\\n            <title>Native Tales</title>\\n            <price>12</price>\\n            <published>2021-11-10</published>\\n            <available>false</available>\\n            <code>B</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <book id=\\\"b3\\\" category=\\\"reference\\\">\\n            <title>Groovy Paths</title>\\n            <price>27</price>\\n            <published>2023-03-18</published>\\n            <available>true</available>\\n            <code>C</code>\\n          </book>\\n          <metrics>\\n            <smallByte>7</smallByte>\\n            <shortNumber>32000</shortNumber>\\n            <longNumber>922337203685477580</longNumber>\\n            <floatNumber>3.5</floatNumber>\\n            <doubleNumber>19.25</doubleNumber>\\n            <uuid>123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000</uuid>\\n          </metrics>\\n        </catalog>\\n        '''\\n\\n    @AfterEach\\n    void resetGlobalConfiguration() {\\n        XmlPath.reset()\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void readsScalarValuesListsMapsAndParameterizedGPathExpressions() {\\n        XmlPath xmlPath = XmlPath.from(CATALOG_XML)\\n\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getString('catalog.@generated')).isEqualTo('true')\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getInt('catalog.book.size()')).isEqualTo(3)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getBoolean('catalog.book[0].available')).isTrue()\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getChar('catalog.book[2].code')).isEqualTo('C' as char)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getByte('catalog.metrics.smallByte')).isEqualTo((byte) 7)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getShort('catalog.metrics.shortNumber')).isEqualTo((short) 32000)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getLong('catalog.metrics.longNumber')).isEqualTo(922337203685477580L)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getFloat('catalog.metrics.floatNumber')).isEqualTo(3.5F)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getDouble('catalog.metrics.doubleNumber')).isEqualTo(19.25D)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getUUID('catalog.metrics.uuid').toString()).isEqualTo('123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000')\\n\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getList('catalog.book.title', String))\\n                .containsExactly('Effective XML', 'Native Tales', 'Groovy Paths')\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getList('catalog.book.price', Integer))\\n                .containsExactly(39, 12, 27)\\n        assertThat(xmlPath.getMap('catalog.book[0].attributes()', String, String))\\n                .containsEntry('id', 'b1')\\n                .containsEntry('category', 'reference')\\n\\n        XmlPath withParameter = xmlPath.param('maximumPrice', 30)\\n        assertThat(withParameter.getList('catalog.book.findAll { it.price.toInteger() <= maximumPrice }.collect { it.@id.toString() }', String))\\n                .containsExactly('b2', 'b3')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void exposesRootNodesNodeChildrenAndRelativeGPathNavigation() {\\n        XmlPath xmlPath = new XmlPath(CATALOG_XML)\\n\\n        Node root = xmlPath.get()\\n        assertThat(root.name()).isEqualTo('catalog')\\n        assertThat(root.getAttribute('generated')).isEqualTo('true')\\n        assertThat(root.children().size()).isEqualTo(4)\\n        assertThat(root.children().isEmpty()).isFalse()\\n\\n        Node firstBook = xmlPath.getNode('catalog.book[0]')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.name()).isEqualTo('book')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.attributes())\\n                .containsEntry('id', 'b1')\\n                .containsEntry('category', 'reference')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getNode('title').value()).isEqualTo('Effective XML')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getNodes('title')).hasSize(1)\\n        assertThat(firstBook.get('@category')).isEqualTo('reference')\\n        assertThat(firstBook.getPath('price', Integer)).isEqualTo(39)\\n        assertThat(firstBook.iterator().next()).isEqualTo('Effective XML')\\n\\n        NodeChildren books = xmlPath.getNodeChildren('catalog.book')\\n        assertThat(books.size()).isEqualTo(3)\\n        assertThat(books.get(1).getAttribute('id')).isEqualTo('b2')\\n        assertThat(books.list()).extracting { Node node -> node.getAttribute('category') }\\n                .containsExactly('reference', 'fiction', 'reference')\\n        assertThat(books.nodeIterable()).extracting { Node node -> node.getNode('title').value() }\\n                .containsExactly('Effective XML', 'Native Tales', 'Groovy Paths')\\n        assertThat(books.nodeIterator().next().name()).isEqualTo('book')\\n        assertThat(books.getPath('findAll { it.@category == \\\"reference\\\" }.title.collect { it.text() }'))\\n                .isEqualTo(['Effective XML', 'Groovy Paths'])\\n        assertThat(books.iterator().next()).contains('Effective XML')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void supportsRootPathAndInputSources(@TempDir Path tempDir) {\\n        String xml = '<root><items><item id=\\\"1\\\">alpha</item><item id=\\\"2\\\">beta</item></items></root>'\\n        Path xmlFile = tempDir.resolve('document.xml')\\n        Files.writeString(xmlFile, xml, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)\\n\\n        XmlPath rootedPath = XmlPath.with(xml).setRootPath('root.items')\\n        assertThat(rootedPath.getInt('item.size()')).isEqualTo(2)\\n        assertThat(rootedPath.getString('item[1]')).isEqualTo('beta')\\n\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.given(new ByteArrayInputStream(xml.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))).getString('root.items.item[0]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('alpha')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(new StringReader(xml)).getString('root.items.item[1].@id'))\\n                .isEqualTo('2')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.with(new InputSource(new StringReader(xml))).getInt('root.items.item.size()'))\\n                .isEqualTo(2)\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.given(xmlFile.toFile()).getString('root.items.item[0]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('alpha')\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(xmlFile.toUri()).getString('root.items.item[1]'))\\n                .isEqualTo('beta')\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void appliesNamespacesDoctypeSettingsAndGlobalConfigurationReset() {\\n        String namespacedXml = '''\\\\\\n            <store xmlns:bk=\\\"urn:books\\\">\\n              <bk:book bk:id=\\\"n1\\\"><bk:title>Namespaced Book</bk:title></bk:book>\\n            </store>\\n            '''\\n        XmlPathConfig namespaceConfig = xmlPathConfig().declaredNamespace('bk', 'urn:books')\\n        XmlPath namespacedPath = new XmlPath(namespacedXml).using(namespaceConfig)\\n\\n        assertThat(namespacedPath.getString(\\\"store.'bk:book'.'bk:title'\\\")).isEqualTo('Namespaced Book')\\n        assertThat(namespaceConfig.declaredNamespaces()).containsEntry('bk', 'urn:books')\\n        assertThat(namespaceConfig.isNamespaceAware()).isTrue()\\n\\n        String documentWithInternalDtd = '''\\\\\\n            <!DOCTYPE note [\\n              <!ELEMENT note (message)>\\n              <!ELEMENT message (#PCDATA)>\\n            ]>\\n            <note><message>Hello from DTD</message></note>\\n            '''\\n        assertThatThrownBy { new XmlPath(documentWithInternalDtd).getString('note.message') }\\n                .isInstanceOf(XmlPathException)\\n\\n        XmlPathConfig dtdConfig = xmlPathConfig().allowDocTypeDeclaration(true).disableLoadingOfExternalDtd()\\n        assertThat(new XmlPath(documentWithInternalDtd).using(dtdConfig).getString('note.message'))\\n                .isEqualTo('Hello from DTD')\\n        assertThat(dtdConfig.features())\\n                .containsEntry('http://apache.org/xml/features/nonvalidating/load-external-dtd', false)\\n\\n        XmlPath.config = dtdConfig\\n        assertThat(XmlPath.from(documentWithInternalDtd).getString('note.message'))\\n                .isEqualTo('Hello from DTD')\\n        XmlPath.reset()\\n        assertThatThrownBy { XmlPath.